[[div class="year-in-review"]]
+ 2025
[[/div]]
[[tabview]]

[[tab February]]
+ Pick of the Month

[[div class="display-container"]]
[[div class="tale-cover"]]
[[image https://i.imgur.com/ZHGQcqW.png link="https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/swords-unto-scramjets"]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="tale-desc"]]
+ Swords unto Scramjets
++++ Written by [[[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/pedantique-personnel-file|Pedantique]]]

//"We're real bastards. They always told us about the Coalition's bloodthirsty ways too."//

The land of Cherinmark reeks of war, even as it enters an uneasy calm, held in precarious balance between the powers that be.

Fantasy meets Foundation meets spy fiction, Swords unto Scramjets deftly weaves a world where the technologies and political ploys of the modern world saturates a fantastical setting, bound with incredibly snappy prose and impeccable verisimilitude.
[[/div]]
[[/div]]
[[/tab]]

[[/tabview]]

[[div class="year-in-review"]]
+ 2024
[[/div]]
[[tabview]]

[[tab January]]
+ Pick of the Month

[[div class="display-container"]]
[[div class="tale-cover"]]
[[image https://i.imgur.com/nF6vPir.png link="https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/hecatoncheires-cycle-hub"]]
[[/div]]
[[div class="tale-desc"]]
+ Hecatoncheires Cycle
++++ Written by [[[grigori-karpin-s-author-page|Grigori Karpin]]]

A touch telepath and a master planner fight a losing war against an otherworldly thaumaturge, an ex-Soviet carnomancer and a long-dormant death cult. They're going to need more hands on deck.

From the ancient world to the technocratic 1990s, this sprawling epic weaves a thrilling mystery full of faith, betrayal, courage and pride. The hand of the past is very much alive, and even dead gods have power in the time of Project Hecatoncheires.

[[span class="complete"]]Completed 2023/11/19[[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]
